Description:
Ballistics of the 23x115mm as fired from the 6-23 6-barreled rotary autocannon. Driven by hydraulic motor, the weapon achieves a rate of fire between 5200-6000 RPM at 21 °C. Barrel length is 1590 mm, cartridge case measure 115mm, travel estimated as the difference. Develops 815 (±10) m/s.

Cartridge is based on the 23x115mm for the AM-23, the projectiles are kept the same. Cartridge material is steel and employs electric primer. Loads 38 grams of 4/7 high-nitration-camphor propellant, develops 2900 kgf/cm² copper crusher gauge, 318.3 MPa piezoelectric. Web 0.38-0.45 mm, perforation diameter 0.13-0.22 mm, length 2.2-3.2 mm. 

Projectiles the same as 23-2 (AM-23), with WB-610P HE-I and WB-611P API-T.
